  "prompt": "Why did Pepper Potts leave Tony Stark in Captain America: Civil War? Why wasn\u2019t she in the film?",
  "response": "In *Captain America: Civil War*, Pepper Potts is notably absent, and her absence is explained through dialogue and context rather than a direct narrative focus on her character. The film suggests that she and Tony Stark (Iron Man) have taken a break from their relationship due to the tensions surrounding the Sokovia Accords and Tony's increasing involvement in superhero conflicts. \n\nIn an earlier scene, it is mentioned that Pepper is \"busy with work\" and engaged in a project that keeps her away from Stark's activities and the Avengers. Additionally, there\u2019s an implied strain on their relationship due to the events of previous films, particularly the fallout from *Avengers: Age of Ultron* and Tony\u2019s relentless dedication to his superhero duties.\n\nGwyneth Paltrow, who plays Pepper Potts, was not involved in the film primarily due to scheduling and her availability. Her character\u2019s absence from the film allowed the narrative to focus more on the conflict between the superhero factions, rather than personal relationships.",
